meta {
  name: GET driving range (per-engine split)
  type: http
  seq: 22
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v2/vehicle-status/{{vin}}/driving-range
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  Per-engine range split — the same shape as CARIAD-BFF but under
  Skoda's mysmob URL. Response keys consumed:
    electricRange.distanceInKm
    combustionRange.distanceInKm  (older firmwares: flat scalar
                                   ``combustionRange``)
    totalRangeInKm
    adBlueRange.distanceInKm

  Drives sensor.<vin>_electric_range_km, _combustion_range_km,
  _total_range_km, _adblue_range_km, plus the headline
  range_km (priority: electric for EV/PHEV → total → combustion).

  Implementation: gathered in SkodaClient.get_status() at
  custom_components/vag_connect/cariad/api/skoda.py:155; parsed in
  the driving_range branch starting around line 322. v1.10.0 (#94)
  added the per-engine split — pre-1.10.0 we read combustionRange
  as a scalar only and got wrong values on Kodiaq iV.
}
